Priest of Set - Advancement
---------------------------

The Order advances those who spill blood in Set's name. Every worthy
kill and every committed prayer bargain earns Priest XP, and your guild level (1 to 20) rises
automatically when you have earned enough.

Earning Priest XP:
- Any NPC kill where you struck the killing blow, or dealt at least a
  tenth of the victim's health, awards Priest XP to everyone in the
  group who qualifies.
- Tougher prey is worth more; prey ten or more levels beneath you is
  worth nothing. Bosses carry large bonuses.
- Variety pays. Hunting the same spawn over and over decays the
  reward; ranging widely keeps it at full value.
- A committed prayer that reserves HP or SP earns one Priest XP per
  ten points of its base reservation, with a minimum of 1 and maximum
  of 25. Prayers with no reservation earn none. Dispensation's added
  reserve does not increase this reward.

Guild levels:
- Levels advance on their own the moment you have earned enough XP.
- Your guild level can never exceed your character level, and your
  combined guild levels can never exceed your character level.
- Set grants nothing to those who walk in the light. XP earned while
  your alignment is good is banked, and the levels pop when you
  return to darkness - just as your prayers demand.
- Guild level 20 is the summit of the priesthood.

Commands:
- 'cost' and 'advance guild' at the Church of Set report your
  progress. Prayers still unlock by guild level; see 'prayers'.

Your record survives leaving the Order. Should you return, your
standing is restored - to the truly evil.
